            <p class="phalaenopsis-subtitle">Growing characteristics</p>
            <p>Phalaenopsis orchids are epiphytes, meaning they naturally grow on tree branches rather than in soil, absorbing moisture and nutrients from the air and rain through their thick, festive roots. They are among the most forgiving orchids for beginners, thriving in bright indirect light with minimal watering – typically once a week. Their flowering cycle lasts several months after which the spike can be cut to encourage reblooming.</p>
